EC contribute to the immune response following virus infection through the production of cytokines and chemokines (Fig. 37.1
). They may also act as antigen presenting cells particularly during secondary respiratory viral infections. Epithelial cells express MHC class I and the costimulatory molecules B7-1 and B7-2 and this expression is upregulated in vitro by RV16 [63] (Fig. 37.2
).
